# Development Workflow

This document outlines development workflows and processes for the Hub project.

## Getting Started

1. Install Node.js 22+ and pnpm 10+
2. Run `pnpm install` to install all dependencies
3. Use `pnpm dev` to start all applications in development mode

## Common Commands

- `pnpm dev` - Start all applications in development mode
- `pnpm build` - Build all applications
- `pnpm lint` - Run ESLint on all packages
- `pnpm lint:fix` - Fix ESLint issues automatically
- `pnpm test` - Run tests across packages

## Versioning

The project uses `semantic-release` for automated release management:

- `pnpm pre-release` - Dry-run release to preview next version
- `pnpm release` - Create a production release

## Docker

A Dockerfile is available for containerized deployment.

## Environment Variables

Environment variables are stored in `.env` files with sensitive values excluded from version control.

## Code Quality Standards
  - Do not add comments unless they provide
  critical context that cannot be understood from
  well-written, semantic code
  - Never disable linting rules without a very good
   reason and detailed explanation
  - Before completing any task, ALWAYS run: pnpm typecheck, pnpm test:unit, pnpm lint